  "timeframe": "15m (with 1m for entry)",
  "market_context": "Post-CPI release on NQ and ES 15-minute charts. NQ took out the prior high into a fair value gap while ES failed to make a higher high, creating a bearish SMT divergence at the highs with equal lows resting below as draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "NQ swept high while ES diverged (SMT). The high-low-higher high-lower low sequence created a 15-minute breaker block; high resistance liquidity above made NQ the preferred short vehicle targeting equal lows.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified bearish SMT divergence at the highs after CPI: NQ took the high into the fair value gap, ES did not.",
    "Recognized the high-low-higher high-lower low structure forming a 15-minute breaker block on NQ.",
    "Chose NQ over ES because NQ swept liquidity, providing high resistance liquidity for the stop placement above the run high.",
    "Placed stop above the high that ran another high rather than directly above the breaker due to CPI volatility and a less-clean breaker.",
    "Targeted the equal lows below on NQ as the draw on liquidity.",
    "Noted price respected the breaker (body did not close over it) and displaced lower with significant range.",
    "For traders who missed the initial entry, dropped to a 1-minute chart inside the 15-minute PD array to find a confirmation entry.",
    "On 1-minute, identified displacement closing below a series of up-close candles — a change in state of delivery.",
    "Chose to enter on the 1-minute fair value gap (rather than at the CISD high) to achieve at least 2R to the original draw on liquidity, since direct entry only gave 1.65R."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade displaced lower respecting the breaker block; setup reached target area toward equal lows with 2R achievable from the 1-minute fair value gap entry.",
  "lessons": "When the initial HTF entry is missed, drop to a lower timeframe inside the HTF PD array and wait for a change in state of delivery, then enter on a fair value gap to secure a minimum 2R to the original draw on liquidity.",
